Mombasa woman representative Mishi Mboko has condemned the disruption of an ODM rally in Migori on Monday.The rally was organised by Suna East MP Junet Mohamed for governor aspirant Ochillo Ayacko.It is alleged that Migori Governor Okoth Obado&rsquo;s supporters caused the chaos in which Mombasa Governor Hassan Joho was allegedly shot at.Obado and Joho have condemned the violence. Joho said it was part of an NIS plan to assassinate him. On Tuesday, Mboko said, &ldquo;We have to embrace democracy.&rdquo; She said barbarism and hooliganism have no place in Kenya. Mboko said everyone has freedom of association.